            "I lift up Leanne to You by name, and I confess the times I have wanted the headship without the cross, the leading without the dying, the love that waits for her to deserve it first. Forgive me. Christ did not wait for the church, and I do not want to wait for my wife. Teach me to love like You, first and sacrificially, and to cherish her as my own body.",
            "Make our marriage cross-shaped. Where there has been ruling, replace it with serving. Where my love has been conditional, make it like Christ's, given before it is earned. Her good is my good, because we are one flesh."
