          "Right before this chapter, the Corinthians were fighting over whose spiritual gifts were better. Paul stops the argument cold and says, you can have every gift, every ability, every act of sacrifice, and if you do not have love, you are nothing. Then he defines what love actually is, line by line.",
          "We end Week 4 here because this is the measuring stick. After three sessions on sacrificial, self-emptying love, Paul gets concrete. He tells you exactly what that love does and does not do. Read slowly, because this chapter has a way of stopping being beautiful and starting to convict the moment you put your own name in it."
