            "I lift up Keith to You by name, and I confess the tallies I keep, the offenses on file, the half-forgiveness that lets go with the mouth but keeps the grip in the heart. Forgive me for being the unforgiving servant, holding small debts while You released my infinite one.",
            "Kill the ledger between us for good. Teach me to forgive him from a forgiven place, freely, repeatedly, without counting. When I am tempted to keep score, remind me how much score You refused to keep against me."
