          "That could land as sad, but it is meant to reframe. Marriage is temporary because it was always pointing to something permanent, the union with Christ that it pictures. The signpost is not the destination. When you arrive, you no longer need the sign.",
          "Then Ecclesiastes gives the other strand. A cord of three strands is not easily broken. The strongest marriage is not two strands wound tightly together. It is two strands plus a third, God Himself, woven through. We pair these because together they tell you how to hold your marriage: precious but not ultimate, and strongest when God is the third strand running through it."
